    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing conducted under at least two independent loading configurations or environmental conditions to bound the operational space; inter-laboratory reproducibility demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted strictly under the single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration at ambient temperature. Although two independent laboratories participated (demonstrating inter-laboratory reproducibility, CV < 4%), only one loading geometry was evaluated. The required Gradation 3 mandates at least two distinct loading configurations to characterize the COU operational envelope; this was not achieved. Achieved level remains Gradation 2. This shortfall was noted by the assessment team but judged not to affect the overall Accepted decision given the strong performance on all remaining factors and the conservative nature of the F1717 protocol relative to in vivo loading."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
