      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements; linkage documented.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load-sharing with the vertebral column; yield force defines the onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm displacement is the ASTM F1717 primary performance metric required by FDA guidance. All three QoIs are directly traceable to clinical failure modes and regulatory requirements. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
